name: "A Name Will Come" EP
description:
Release date 4 April 2008

The debut EP was recorded in the misty hills of Bilambil, at the southern end of the Gold Coast, Australia. The recording was engineered, mixed and produced by Govinda Doyle (Angus & Julia Stone, Dallas Frasca). Mastered at Turtlerock Mastering (Silverchair, You Am I, Faith No More) in Sydney.


Tracklisting

1. Cemetery Forest
2. Brand New Blinded
3. Cupid
4. Hill of Skulls
5. Breaking Bread

Recording also features a bonus acoustic complement to "Breaking Bread".
